1513
01:32:09,520 --> 01:32:11,431
You're keeping it going by hook or by crook.

1514
01:32:11,480 --> 01:32:14,278
All right, what do you suggest?
Suicide or murder?

1515
01:32:14,320 --> 01:32:16,595
Neither. Just honesty.

1516
01:32:16,640 --> 01:32:18,835
Last night, a party. Tonight, you'll tuck her in.

1517
01:32:18,880 --> 01:32:21,792
We have separate rooms. You know that.
You've asked about it...

1518
01:32:21,840 --> 01:32:24,718
I don't care whether you have separate rooms,
beds, gas ovens!

1519
01:32:24,760 --> 01:32:29,231
I just don't want her name bandied around here
and her wants and her parties and her needs.

1520
01:32:29,280 --> 01:32:32,431
Maybe she'd like me to sit on the end of the bed
to honour the proceedings.

1521
01:32:32,480 --> 01:32:34,232
I'll put it to her.

1522
01:32:43,440 --> 01:32:45,317
I don't want to see you like this.

1523
01:32:47,240 --> 01:32:49,276
And I don't want to be seen like this.

1524
01:32:51,080 --> 01:32:54,959
You're everything I've ever despised
and I've become everything I vowed never to be.

1525
01:32:55,000 --> 01:32:56,991
That's where our love has got us.

1526
01:32:59,480 --> 01:33:00,879
<i>Right.</i>

1527
01:33:00,920 --> 01:33:02,751
That's it, then.

1528
01:33:04,080 --> 01:33:05,718
Let's forget it.

1529
01:33:07,800 --> 01:33:11,793
Look, I... I didn't set out to fall in love with you.

1530
01:33:12,960 --> 01:33:15,190
I set out to have an affair.

1531
01:33:15,240 --> 01:33:17,913
A little bit on the side,
the sort of thing a man wants.

1532
01:33:19,320 --> 01:33:22,312
But I did...fall in love with you.

1533
01:33:24,040 --> 01:33:25,712
That's what happened.

1534
01:33:25,760 --> 01:33:27,830
And that's the way it stands.

1535
01:33:29,360 --> 01:33:32,079
As for the other things...her life, my life,

1536
01:33:32,120 --> 01:33:33,553
well...

1537
01:33:34,360 --> 01:33:36,191
it's all junk.

1538
01:33:36,240 --> 01:33:38,515
It's a mess and I don't want it.

1539
01:33:40,640 --> 01:33:42,437
But I've got it.

1540
01:33:51,480 --> 01:33:54,153
I wish now you'd let her die.

1541
01:34:12,000 --> 01:34:13,911
Hello. Rita?

1542
01:34:13,960 --> 01:34:16,076
This is your boss.

1543
01:34:16,120 --> 01:34:17,838
<i>What's going on up there?</i>

1544
01:34:17,880 --> 01:34:21,429
There's been several phone calls for you.
Mr Nelson has some drawings...

1545
01:34:21,480 --> 01:34:23,471
Never mind that.

1546
01:34:23,520 --> 01:34:25,670
I want you to come and have lunch with me.

1547
01:34:26,600 --> 01:34:27,999
Where?

1548
01:34:28,040 --> 01:34:29,598
Well, you know where.

1549
01:34:29,640 --> 01:34:32,200
The same place where we always have lunch.

1550
01:34:33,240 --> 01:34:35,071
All right.

1551
01:34:35,120 --> 01:34:38,351
But it'll take about 15 to 20 minutes to get there.

1552
01:34:38,400 --> 01:34:39,913
I'll wait.

1553
01:35:13,800 --> 01:35:16,837
Your front door was open, sol let myself in.

1554
01:35:17,560 --> 01:35:20,791
<i>I went over to your other piece,
but they said you'd moved.</i>

1555
01:35:22,400 --> 01:35:23,992
Very nice.

1556
01:35:24,760 --> 01:35:25,829
Clean.

1557
01:35:27,280 --> 01:35:28,713
New.

1558
01:35:29,880 --> 01:35:31,518
What do you want, Zee?

1559
01:35:33,880 --> 01:35:35,757
What do we both want?

1560
01:35:42,680 --> 01:35:44,511
I expected to hear from you...

1561
01:35:45,560 --> 01:35:48,393
...after our little talk in hospital.

1562
01:35:50,480 --> 01:35:52,152
I don't know what...

1563
01:35:52,200 --> 01:35:54,316
What on earth are you talking about?

1564
01:35:59,800 --> 01:36:04,351
A girl has to be quite grown up
to be expelled for kissing a nun.

1565
01:36:07,840 --> 01:36:09,512
How old were you, Stella?

1566
01:36:14,400 --> 01:36:16,391
I'm sorry, Zee...

1567
01:36:17,320 --> 01:36:19,595
...I don't see that that's any of your business.

1568
01:36:22,640 --> 01:36:25,712
A child can't be expelled for falling in love.

1569
01:36:26,720 --> 01:36:29,553
If you were 15...16...

1570
01:36:30,600 --> 01:36:32,192
...well, then...

1571
01:36:33,240 --> 01:36:35,993
And maybe there were other things.

1572
01:36:37,040 --> 01:36:39,634
<i>Other girls at school that</i> you...

1573
01:36:39,680 --> 01:36:41,352
fell in love with.

1574
01:36:46,800 --> 01:36:48,438
You can tell me, love.

1575
01:36:49,120 --> 01:36:50,678
We're friends.

1576
01:36:55,680 --> 01:36:57,238
There's nothing to tell.

1577
01:36:58,240 --> 01:37:00,674
Oh, come on, Stella.

1578
01:37:01,720 --> 01:37:03,756
Don't make it so difficult for me.

1579
01:37:16,040 --> 01:37:17,519
You're crazy.

1580
01:37:21,640 --> 01:37:23,278
Aren't we all, love?

1581
01:37:24,600 --> 01:37:26,033
Just a little.

1582
01:37:38,480 --> 01:37:40,516
<i>ROBERT. Yeah, I called her at the flat.</i>

1583
01:37:40,560 --> 01:37:43,074
<i>The telephone was out of order.</i>

1584
01:37:43,120 --> 01:37:47,398
Look, if you hear from her,
would you tell her I called, please?

1585
01:37:47,440 --> 01:37:49,032
Yeah, OK, thank you.

1586
01:37:49,080 --> 01:37:50,479
Goodbye.

1587
01:37:57,760 --> 01:38:02,550
Well...I'm gonna have to get dressed
and get out of here...

1588
01:38:03,640 --> 01:38:05,631
...before your young man arrives.

1589
01:38:06,760 --> 01:38:08,751
I don't have to answer the door.

1590
01:38:08,800 --> 01:38:11,109
He'll think I'm still working.

1591
01:38:12,120 --> 01:38:13,951
Don't be greedy.

1592
01:38:14,960 --> 01:38:18,714
Besides which, that would be dishonest.

1593
01:38:37,680 --> 01:38:39,671
- All right?
- Yes, guv. Thanks.

1594
01:38:55,000 --> 01:38:56,718
Stella.

1595
01:38:56,760 --> 01:38:59,194
Stella, stop being silly.

1596
01:39:00,280 --> 01:39:01,838
Open the door.

1597
01:39:03,240 --> 01:39:04,832
Stella!

1598
01:39:16,760 --> 01:39:18,398
What are you doing here?

1599
01:39:18,440 --> 01:39:20,032
Oh, just...

1600
01:39:20,720 --> 01:39:22,392
paying a little social visit.

1601
01:39:27,960 --> 01:39:29,359
Where's Stella?

1602
01:39:30,480 --> 01:39:32,357
In the bedroom.

1603
01:39:46,080 --> 01:39:48,036
(Wind chimes)

1604
01:39:48,080 --> 01:39:49,638
Stella?

1605
01:40:02,800 --> 01:40:04,518
Stella.

1606
01:40:11,640 --> 01:40:13,073
Stella.

1607
01:40:15,320 --> 01:40:17,038
Leave me alone.

1608
01:40:17,080 --> 01:40:18,752
Please.

1609
01:40:25,440 --> 01:40:27,431
(Phone crackles)

1610
01:40:53,960 --> 01:40:55,791
What happened?

1611
01:41:01,680 --> 01:41:03,272
I don't know.

1612
01:41:06,560 --> 01:41:08,949
- Listen, Stella...
(Zee clears her throat)

1613
01:41:12,640 --> 01:41:16,599
Don't worry.
She's a bit confused right now, Bobby.

1614
01:41:17,400 --> 01:41:19,277
But she'll be all right in a couple of days.

1615
01:41:19,320 --> 01:41:22,198
<i>Then maybe we can all get together...</i>

1616
01:41:22,240 --> 01:41:24,595
and talk over old times...

1617
01:41:24,640 --> 01:41:26,596
old loves.

1618
01:41:34,160 --> 01:41:35,798
Come on, Daddy.

1619
01:41:39,320 --> 01:41:41,390
Baby wants something to eat.

1620
01:41:45,480 --> 01:41:47,630
It's been one hell of a day.

1621
01:41:51,920 --> 01:41:53,399
Coming?

1622
01:42:08,240 --> 01:42:11,437
♪ I'm going in circles

1623
01:42:11,480 --> 01:42:15,712
♪ I don't really know

1624
01:42:15,760 --> 01:42:18,149
♪ Where have I come from?

1625
01:42:19,520 --> 01:42:22,239
♪ Where will I go?

1626
01:42:22,280 --> 01:42:25,909
♪ You say that you love me

1627
01:42:26,440 --> 01:42:29,352
♪ Well, maybe you do

1628
01:42:30,120 --> 01:42:33,078
♪ There's nothing that matters

1629
01:42:33,680 --> 01:42:37,753
♪ Or anything new

1630
01:42:40,800 --> 01:42:47,638
♪ I've been through a million trips in the night

1631
01:42:48,320 --> 01:42:51,039
♪ Living with shadows

1632
01:42:51,680 --> 01:42:54,752
♪ Looking for light

1633
01:42:55,560 --> 01:42:58,518
♪ Passing the faces

1634
01:42:58,960 --> 01:43:01,793
♪ How lonely they seem

1635
01:43:02,640 --> 01:43:05,552
♪ Looking for traces

1636
01:43:06,080 --> 01:43:09,789
♪ Of yesterday's dream

1637
01:43:13,240 --> 01:43:15,993
♪ I'm going in circles

1638
01:43:16,760 --> 01:43:19,638
♪ I've been here before

1639
01:43:20,400 --> 01:43:23,198
♪ Never expected

1640
01:43:24,200 --> 01:43:27,033
♪ Anything more

1641
01:43:27,680 --> 01:43:30,513
♪ I might die tomorrow

1642
01:43:31,080 --> 01:43:34,197
♪ I might go to Spain, yeah

1643
01:43:34,640 --> 01:43:37,757
♪ I'm numb to the sorrow

1644
01:43:38,320 --> 01:43:42,518
♪ And numb to the pain

1645
01:43:42,560 --> 01:43:44,551
♪ Yeah